cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.AI, cs.MM

Reasoning: The paper deals with image-set matching, which is a problem in computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also introduces a supervised dimensionality reduction technique, which suggests that it may belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of Csiszar f-divergences and kernel density estimators indicates that the paper may also belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the experiments involve video-based face recognition and dynamic texture classification, which suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia).
